<TITLE> Bijoy Sarani-Tejgaon Link Road opened </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 20 (bdnews24.com)  The Bijoy Sarani-Tejgaon Link Road was opened on Tuesday. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina launched the much-awaited 1,114 metres long road shortly before midday. This road will connect Bijoy Sarani with Shahid Tajuddin road (Mahakhali-Maghbazar road). This will allow traffic to go to the Tejgaon industrial zone from the capital's mid-west area without having to go via Mahakhali or Karwan Bazar. The construction of the road, which cost Tk 114 crore, began after the demolition of the Rangs Bahban in 2008 during the caretaker government regim
